meta {
  name: Turns Per Session Breach
  type: http
  seq: 2
}

post {
  url: {{base_url}}/chat
  body: json
  auth: bearer
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{auth_token}}
}

body:json {
  {
    "message": "what should I eat tonight?"
  }
}

docs {
  ## Precondition
  User's `turns` counter must be at or above the plan threshold (10 for homebody).
  Sessions and tool_calls must be below their respective thresholds so only turns triggers.

  ## Expected Response
  HTTP 429 — Too Many Requests

  ```json
  {
    "error": "rate_limit_exceeded",
    "limit": "turns_per_session",
    "limit_value": 10
  }
  ```

  ## Notes
  - Guard checks tool_calls first, then turns, then sessions — ensure tool_calls is under limit
  - Turns accumulate in ChatService BEFORE the FastAPI call (consumed even on error)
  - NestJS server must be running on port 3333: `pnpm nx serve api`
}
